<div class="instructions-container">
  <h2>How to Use Party Spheres</h2>

  <h3>Getting Started</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Click the <strong>ACCOUNT</strong> button on the homepage.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Sign up here</strong> to create an account.</li>
    <li>Log in with your new username and password.</li>
    <li>Use the navigation bar or homepage buttons to explore.</li>
    <li><strong>Home</strong> returns you to the main page of the game.</li>
    <li><strong>Leaderboard</strong> shows you top players — including yourself if your score is high enough.</li>
    <li><strong>Characters</strong> lets you view the characters you'll interact with and gives you some lore for each one.</li>  
    <li><strong>Players</strong> lets you see other users and information on their profiles.</li>
    <li><strong>Account</strong> displays your account details when you're signed in.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Playing the Game</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Click <strong>PLAY GAME</strong> to begin a new session.</li>
    <li>You'll see three “Spheres” of characters. Click one to choose.</li>
    <li>Select an action: Compliment, Invite, or Help.</li>
    <li>Match NPC preferences for maximum points:
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Green “C”</strong> = Likes Compliments</li>
        <li><strong>Yellow “I”</strong> = Neutral to Invites</li>
        <li><strong>Red “H”</strong> = Dislikes Help</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>The Happiness bar drains every 4 seconds — keep it full by making good moves.</li>
    <li>The game ends when happiness reaches 0. Try to beat your high score!</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Characters</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Characters</strong> page to view all characters.</li>
    <li>Click any character to see their likes, dislikes, and lore.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Profiles & Players</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Visit the <strong>Players</strong> page to explore user profiles.</li>
    <li>Click on a username to view their public profile and stats.</li>
    <li>Use the <strong>Leaderboard</strong> to compare high scores.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Managing Your Account</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Click the <strong>ACCOUNT</strong> button to view your profile.</li>
    <li>You can update your username, email, password, bio, and profile image.</li>
    <li>If you forget your login info, use the recovery option on the <strong>Login</strong> page (the link on the bottom).</li>
  </ul>
</div>

